  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 32 g
  protein: 48 g
course: main course
cuisine: European
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/mozzarella-stuffed-beefburgers-54db6e3a6ced6e541f8b456d
time required: 20 minutes
---

Cut your @cherry tomatoes{1}(cut in half) and then peel and finely dice your @garlic clove{1}. Cut one ball of @mozzarella{2} into four slices from the first ball (i.e. you will have one ball left).

Mix your @British beef mince{450%g} thoroughly with the garlic, @dried oregano{2} and @mustard{1/2%tsp}. Add @salt{1/4%tsp} and some freshly ground @black pepper{}. Work the mixture with your hands for a couple of minutes to fully mix all of the ingredients. Pre-heat your #grill{} to high.

> As you're making four burgers, divide your burger mixture into four and press each into the shape of a burger.

Press the burger into your hand to make a shallow cup and put a slice of your mozzarella in the middle. Now close the meat around the mozzarella so that you end up with a stuffed burger.

Rub a small amount of @olive oil{} on each burger and then place these on a #baking tray{}. Place under the grill and cook them for around ~{4%minutes} on each side.

> Any more and you risk them having the texture of a Bedouin's flip-flop.

Cut your @ciabatta{2} in half lengthways and then cut each piece in half again to make your burger baps. Grill these for about ~{1%minute} on each side until they are lightly toasted.

Cut up the @baby gem lettuce{2} and tear up your @basil{1}. Mix these and the tomatoes together gently, with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Lastly, tear up the remaining mozzarella with your fingers and add this too.

Serve and devour with reckless abandon.